<refnamediv><refname>dnn_topk</refname><refpurpose>Return top K scores and indices.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>[scores, indices, labels] = dnn_topk(x, k, labels)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>dnn_topk</function> sorts a score vector in descending order and returns the top entries.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
[scores, indices] = dnn_topk([0.1; 0.8; 0.2], 2);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
